{"parse":{"title":"Garnddyrys Forge","pageid":50158482,"revid":753100153,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption class=\"fn org\">Garnddyrys Forge</caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Garnddyrys,_ironworks_remains_and_tramroad,_Blorenge,_Llanfoist_Fawr.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Garnddyrys, ironworks remains and tramroad, Blorenge, Llanfoist Fawr.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Garnddyrys%2C_ironworks_remains_and_tramroad%2C_Blorenge%2C_Llanfoist_Fawr.jpg/220px-Garnddyrys%2C_ironworks_remains_and_tramroad%2C_Blorenge%2C_Llanfoist_Fawr.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"127\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Garnddyrys%2C_ironworks_remains_and_tramroad%2C_Blorenge%2C_Llanfoist_Fawr.jpg/330px-Garnddyrys%2C_ironworks_remains_and_tramroad%2C_Blorenge%2C_Llanfoist_Fawr.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Garnddyrys%2C_ironworks_remains_and_tramroad%2C_Blorenge%2C_Llanfoist_Fawr.jpg/440px-Garnddyrys%2C_ironworks_remains_and_tramroad%2C_Blorenge%2C_Llanfoist_Fawr.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3516\" data-file-height=\"2034\" /></a><div>Remains of the ironworks and tramroad</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<div class=\"center\"><div style=\"width:235px;float:none;clear:both;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\"><div style=\"width:235px;padding:0\"><div style=\"position:relative;width:235px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Monmouthshire_UK_relief_location_map.jpg\" class=\"image\" title=\"Garnddyrys Forge is located in Monmouthshire\"><img alt=\"Garnddyrys Forge is located in Monmouthshire\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Monmouthshire_UK_relief_location_map.jpg/235px-Monmouthshire_UK_relief_location_map.jpg\" width=\"235\" height=\"313\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Monmouthshire_UK_relief_location_map.jpg/353px-Monmouthshire_UK_relief_location_map.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Monmouthshire_UK_relief_location_map.jpg/470px-Monmouthshire_UK_relief_location_map.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2004\" data-file-height=\"2672\" /></a><div style=\"position:absolute;top:39.715%;left:20.514%\"><div style=\"position:absolute;left:-4px;top:-4px;line-height:0\"><img alt=\"Garnddyrys Forge\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/Red_pog.svg/8px-Red_pog.svg.png\" title=\"Garnddyrys Forge\" width=\"8\" height=\"8\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/Red_pog.svg/12px-Red_pog.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/Red_pog.svg/16px-Red_pog.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"64\" data-file-height=\"64\" /></div></div></div><div>Location of Garnddyrys Forge</div></div></div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Operated</th><td>\n1817\u201361</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Coordinates</th><td>\n<span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Garnddyrys_Forge&amp;params=51.801423_N_3.0769175_W_type:landmark\"><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">51\u00b048\u203205\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">3\u00b004\u203237\u2033W</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">51.801423\u00b0N 3.0769175\u00b0W</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">51.801423; -3.0769175</span></span></span></a></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span id=\"coordinates\"><a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">Coordinates</a>: <span class=\"plainlinks nourlexpansion\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Garnddyrys_Forge&amp;params=51.801423_N_3.0769175_W_type:landmark\"><span class=\"geo-nondefault\"><span class=\"geo-dms\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\"><span class=\"latitude\">51\u00b048\u203205\u2033N</span> <span class=\"longitude\">3\u00b004\u203237\u2033W</span></span></span><span class=\"geo-multi-punct\">&#xfeff; / &#xfeff;</span><span class=\"geo-default\"><span class=\"geo-dec\" title=\"Maps, aerial photos, and other data for this location\">51.801423\u00b0N 3.0769175\u00b0W</span><span style=\"display:none\">&#xfeff; / <span class=\"geo\">51.801423; -3.0769175</span></span></span></a></span></span></span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Industry</th><td class=\"category\">\nIron foundry</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Products</th><td>\nWrought iron</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Garnddyrys Forge</b> was an iron foundry in Wales that operated from about 1817\u201360 near <a href=\"/wiki/Blaenavon\" title=\"Blaenavon\">Blaenavon</a> in Wales, lying on a tramroad between Blaenavon and the Brecknock and Abergavenny Canal. At one time 450 people lived around the ironworks. It became isolated when the railway took a different route to Blaenavon, and was abandoned. Although little now is visible, it is archaeologically well-preserved.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_years\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent years</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Sources\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sources</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Garnddyrys_Forge&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In response to a surge in demand for iron during the <a href=\"/wiki/Napoleonic_Wars\" title=\"Napoleonic Wars\">Napoleonic Wars</a> the manager of the <a href=\"/wiki/Blaenavon_Ironworks\" title=\"Blaenavon Ironworks\">Blaenavon Ironworks</a>, Thomas Hill II, built what became called <a href=\"/wiki/Hill%27s_Tramroad\" title=\"Hill&#39;s Tramroad\">Hill's Tramroad</a> from Pwll Du to the <a href=\"/wiki/Llanfoist\" title=\"Llanfoist\">Llanfoist</a> wharf around 1815.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHLCA_011_Blorenge_and_Gilwern_Hill_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEHLCA_011_Blorenge_and_Gilwern_Hill-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\nThis linked Blaenavon via Pwll Du and Garnddyrys to the <a href=\"/wiki/Brecknock_and_Abergavenny_Canal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brecknock and Abergavenny Canal\">Brecknock and Abergavenny Canal</a>.\nThe tramroad passed through the Garnddyrys site in a tunnel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\nIt connected Blaenavon to limestone quarries at Pwll-Du and <a href=\"/wiki/Tyla\" title=\"Tyla\">Tyla</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEThomas_Hill\u2019s_Tram_Road_\u2013_Visit_Blaenavon_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEThomas_Hill\u2019s_Tram_Road_\u2013_Visit_Blaenavon-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\nIt then ran for 3 miles (4.8&#160;km) north east from Pwll Du round the <a href=\"/wiki/Blorenge\" title=\"Blorenge\">Blorenge</a> hill to Llanfoist Wharf.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTENewman2000126_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTENewman2000126-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Garnddyrys Forge<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;a&#93;</a></sup> was built by Thomas Hill II in 1816\u201317.\nThe market for iron was very weak at the time, so the investment was unusual.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\nThe plans to build the forge in Cwm Llanwenarth on the west branch of the Blorenge included replacing a steeply sloped section of the tramroad from Blaenavon by a shallow gradient tramroad along the <a href=\"/wiki/Pwll_Du_Tunnel\" title=\"Pwll Du Tunnel\">Pwll Du Tunnel</a>, an extension of an  earlier mine tunnel through the hill to <a href=\"/wiki/Pwll_Du\" title=\"Pwll Du\">Pwll Du</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGardener2001_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGardener2001-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\nThe tramroad brought cast iron from  <a href=\"/wiki/Blaenavon\" title=\"Blaenavon\">Blaenavon</a> and took wrought iron from the forge to the Llanfoist wharf.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>By the 1840s there were about 450 people living around the Garnddyrys Forge.\nGarnddyrys became isolated in 1854 when the railway reached <a href=\"/wiki/Blaenavon\" title=\"Blaenavon\">Blaenavon</a>.\nA replacement forge, called Forgeside, was built near the railway in Blaenavon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\nIn 1860 the Garnddyrys works were closed, the forge was relocated to Forgeside, Blaenavon, and the northern branch of the tunnel at Pwll Du was closed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGardener2001_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGardener2001-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_years\">Recent years</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Garnddyrys_Forge&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Recent years\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The site was abandoned, and is thus important as an archaeologically well-preserved forge from the early 19th century.\nIn 1970 the foundations of the worker's houses were excavated.\nThe site includes two reservoirs, the sites of waterwheels and reservoirs, and worker's housing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Garnddyrys_Forge&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/wiki/Alexander_Cordell\" title=\"Alexander Cordell\">Alexander Cordell</a> made the Garnddyrys Forge famous in his <i><a href=\"/wiki/Rape_of_the_Fair_Country\" title=\"Rape of the Fair Country\">Rape of the Fair Country</a></i> (1959).<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGardener2001_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGardener2001-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> </span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div><div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEHLCA_011_Blorenge_and_Gilwern_Hill-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHLCA_011_Blorenge_and_Gilwern_Hill_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFHLCA_011_Blorenge_and_Gilwern_Hill\">HLCA 011 Blorenge and Gilwern Hill</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein_2-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein\">Garnddyrys Forge, Blorenge \u2013 Coflein</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEThomas_Hill\u2019s_Tram_Road_\u2013_Visit_Blaenavon-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEThomas_Hill\u2019s_Tram_Road_\u2013_Visit_Blaenavon_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFThomas_Hill\u2019s_Tram_Road_\u2013_Visit_Blaenavon\">Thomas Hill\u2019s Tram Road \u2013 Visit Blaenavon</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTENewman2000126-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTENewman2000126_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFNewman2000\">Newman 2000</a>, p.&#160;126.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEGardener2001-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGardener2001_5-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGardener2001_5-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGardener2001_5-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFGardener2001\">Gardener 2001</a>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Garnddyrys_Forge&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r853264625\">.mw-parser-output .refbegin{font-size:90%;margin-bottom:0.5em}.mw-parser-output .refbegin-hanging-indents>ul{list-style-type:none;margin-left:0}.mw-parser-output .refbegin-hanging-indents>ul>li,.mw-parser-output .refbegin-hanging-indents>dl>dd{margin-left:0;padding-left:3.2em;text-indent:-3.2em;list-style:none}.mw-parser-output .refbegin-100{font-size:100%}</style><div class=\"refbegin\" style=\"\">\n<ul><li><cite id=\"CITEREFGarnddyrys_Forge,_Blorenge_\u2013_Coflein\" class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.coflein.gov.uk/en/site/34137/details/GARNDDYRYS+FORGE,+BLORENGE/\">\"Garnddyrys Forge, Blorenge\"</a>, <i>Coflein</i>, <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Commission_on_the_Ancient_and_Historical_Monuments_of_Wales\" title=\"Royal Commission on the Ancient and Historical Monuments of Wales\">Royal Commission on the Ancient and Historical Monuments of Wales</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">, retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2016-04-13</span></span></cite><span